O:9:"MagpieRSS":23:{s:6:"parser";i:0;s:12:"current_item";a:0:{}s:5:"items";a:50:{i:0;a:14:{s:5:"title";s:49:"IE9 Gets 2.35 Million Downloads in First 24 Hours";s:4:"link";s:74:"http://www.windows7news.com/2011/03/17/ie9-235-million-downloads-24-hours/";s:8:"comments";s:83:"http://www.windows7news.com/2011/03/17/ie9-235-million-downloads-24-hours/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Thu, 17 Mar 2011 12:20:25 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:17:"Mike Halsey (MVP)";}s:8:"category";s:40:"Windows 7 SoftwareieIE9internet explorer";s:4:"guid";s:36:"http://www.windows7news.com/?p=10949";s:11:"description";s:336:"Microsoft have been touting their new web browser for quite some time now and they&#8217;ve managed to get a considerable volume of publicity for it around the world.  Despite usage figures that have dropped sharply in the last five years it still remains the world&#8217;s most used web browser.  The latest version 9, which will [...]";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:4944:"<p><a href="http://wincom.eurekaconsultinglimited.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/internetexplorer9logo1.png"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-10950" src="http://wincom.eurekaconsultinglimited.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/internetexplorer9logo1-150x150.png" alt="internetexplorer9logo1 150x150 IE9 Gets 2.35 Million Downloads in First 24 Hours" width="150" height="150" title="IE9 Gets 2.35 Million Downloads in First 24 Hours" /></a>Microsoft have been touting their new web browser for quite some time now and they&#8217;ve managed to get a considerable volume of publicity for it around the world.  Despite usage figures that have dropped sharply in the last five years it still remains the world&#8217;s most used web browser.  The latest version 9, which will only run on Windows Vista and Windows 7, was released this week and now Microsoft have said the browser had 2.35 million downloads from the Microsoft website in the first 24 hours after release.</p>
<p>This figure doesn&#8217;t include the people who had previously downloaded the release candidate, nor does it include people who would have downloaded it to try it, but would then go back to a different browser.</p>
<p>In their blog, Microsoft said&#8230;</p>
<blockquote><p>We want to thank everyone around the world for downloading IE9 and the enthusiastic reception. 2.3 million downloads in 24 hours is over double the 1 million downloads we saw of the IE9 Beta and four times that of the IE9 RC over the same time period.</p></blockquote>
<p>The battle is now back on, at least that&#8217;s what Microsoft strongly want us to believe but it&#8217;s not too much of a stretch to see why this time they have a good point.  Internet Explorer 9 is an excellent browser and it finally brings IE up to the standards that rivals Firefox and Chrome have been maintaining for years.</p>
<p>We&#8217;ll watch the growth of the new browser here at Windows7News and see if in the next quarter Microsoft are able to claw back some of the market share they&#8217;ve been losing month-on-month for the last few years.</p>


