</div>";s:14:"date_timestamp";i:1300300414;}i:3;a:14:{s:5:"title";s:45:"Microsoft Cloud Efforts Slowly Building Steam";s:4:"link";s:85:"http://www.windows7news.com/2011/03/15/microsoft-cloud-efforts-slowly-building-steam/";s:8:"comments";s:94:"http://www.windows7news.com/2011/03/15/microsoft-cloud-efforts-slowly-building-steam/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Tue, 15 Mar 2011 15:00:49 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:6:"GGarza";}s:8:"category";s:33:"Windows 7 NewsAzurecloudMicrosoft";s:4:"guid";s:36:"http://www.windows7news.com/?p=10936";s:11:"description";s:301:"With Microsoft cloud apps, people can work together from virtually anywhere, across a range of devices.  Also, unlike ?pure cloud? solutions, Microsoft's online solutions for productivity work can with software that organizations currently have, so they can transition to the cloud on their own terms.";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:6501:"<p>More companies are getting involved with Microsoft Cloud. Four Companies, Shell, Manpower, Tampa General Hospital and Advocate Health Care have announced plans to move some operations to the cloud.</p>
<p><a href="http://wincom.eurekaconsultinglimited.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Microsoft-Cloud.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-10937" src="http://wincom.eurekaconsultinglimited.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Microsoft-Cloud-400x186.jpg" alt="Microsoft Cloud 400x186 Microsoft Cloud Efforts Slowly Building Steam" width="400" height="186" title="Microsoft Cloud Efforts Slowly Building Steam" /></a></p>
<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>
<p>With Microsoft cloud apps, people can work together from virtually  anywhere, across a range of devices.  Also, unlike ?pure cloud? solutions, Microsoft&#8217;s online solutions for productivity work can with software that organizations currently have, so they can transition to the cloud on their own terms.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Microsoft Business Productivity Online Suite (BPOS)</strong></p>
<p>BPOS is available in 40 countries and regions. This software suite includes Microsoft Exchange  Online, Microsoft SharePoint Online, Microsoft Office Live Meeting and  Microsoft Office Communications Online. It offers several benefits to companies such as increased  productivity, tighter security, and the opportunity to remain current with the latest  technologies.</p>
<p><strong>Manpower</strong></p>
<p>It is easy to how Manpower, an employment agency, can benefit from cloud applications. They have locations in most states, and they are always looking to fill job openings or matching potential recruits to individual jobs. Now with cloud access, an office in Phoenix can match the credentials with a recruit in a different state. Both the office and the recruit can benefit from this.</p>
<p><strong>Tampa General Hospital</strong></p>
<p>A healthcare organization knows that their physicians, nurses and other employees travel a lot, and the hospital wants to give their medical staff and other employees the ability to work where they are,  on virtually any PC, browser or mobile device they use.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Advocate Health Care</strong></p>
<p>Another health care provider moved to the Microsoft cloud. Advocate Health Care is the largest health care provider in Illinois. It has 29,000  employees working across multiple locations. One of the things that they wanted to  improve upon with the messaging technology to make sure its clinicians could  communicate clearly, quickly and accurately. They moved to decommission their old  e-mail servers and gave their employees  subscriptions to Microsoft Exchange Online.</p>
<p><strong>Shell</strong></p>
<p>Shell also made the move to the cloud using Microsoft SharePoint Online  and Microsoft SharePoint 2010 to enable global, online collaboration  among employees.This will allow  a central platform for various applications to be instituted. It will include  document and content management, and it will  let different offices in the organization do  collaboration in project work.</p>
<p><strong>Other Companies in the Microsoft Cloud</strong></p>
<p>This new list adds to the already growing number of customers that have made the move to the Microsoft Cloud. Those companies include AON Insurance, The Dow Chemical Co., GAP Inc., Hyatt Corp.,  Kraft Foods Inc., Vanderbilt University, and the states of California  and Minnesota, along with many  small and midsized businesses.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Source: <a href="http://www.microsoft.com/Presspass/press/2011/mar11/03-10CustomerCloudAppsPR.mspx">Microsoft</a></p>
<p>You can read about <a href="http://www.microsoft.com/business/bposoffer/?CR_CC=200027254&amp;WT.srch=1">BPOS here</a>.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>


