</div>";s:14:"date_timestamp";i:1299815128;}i:14;a:14:{s:5:"title";s:35:"SP1 for Visual Studio 2010 Released";s:4:"link";s:71:"http://www.windows7news.com/2011/03/08/sp1-visual-studio-2010-released/";s:8:"comments";s:80:"http://www.windows7news.com/2011/03/08/sp1-visual-studio-2010-released/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Wed, 09 Mar 2011 01:39:22 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:6:"GGarza";}s:8:"category";s:30:"Windows 7 NewsSP1Visual Studio";s:4:"guid";s:36:"http://www.windows7news.com/?p=10908";s:11:"description";s:376:"On March 8, MSDN subscribers will be able to download and install Service Pack 1 (SP1).  Furthermore, MSDN subscribers  will also be able to download the Team Foundation Server Integration Feature Pack, which facilitates the integration of  three environments, namely Visual Studio, Project and SharePoint. What is Visual Studio? Microsoft Visual Studio is an Integrated [...]";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:5570:"<p>On March 8, MSDN subscribers will be able to download and install Service Pack 1 (SP1).  Furthermore, MSDN subscribers  will also be able to download the Team Foundation Server Integration Feature Pack, which facilitates the integration of  three environments, namely Visual Studio, Project and SharePoint.</p>
<p><a href="http://wincom.eurekaconsultinglimited.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/VisualStudio.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-10909" src="http://wincom.eurekaconsultinglimited.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/VisualStudio-400x254.png" alt="VisualStudio 400x254 SP1 for Visual Studio 2010 Released" width="400" height="254" title="SP1 for Visual Studio 2010 Released" /></a></p>
<p><strong>What is Visual Studio?</strong></p>
<p>Microsoft Visual Studio is an Integrated Development Environment (IDE). It can be used to develop console and graphical user interface applications as well as Windows Forms applications, web sites, web applications, and web services in both native code together with managed code. This development environment comes with two standard programming languages Visual Basic and C#.</p>
<p><strong>What does SP1 have?</strong></p>
<p>Visual Studio SP1, which has been in beta since December 2010, includes support for Silverlight 3 and 4 tools; plus the tools for Windows 7-specific Microsoft Foundation Class programming interfaces to support use of Direct2D, DirectWrite, and Windows Animation; it also has a new local Help Viewer.</p>
<p>There is also a feature pack that developers will be happy with. With the pack  developers can simulate as many virtual users as needed without having to purchase additional Visual Studio Load Test Virtual User Pack 2010 licenses. Testing applications with a gamut of simulated users will supply developers a real-world view of the performance of their application, before it goes to production.</p>
<p><strong>Application Development Tools</strong></p>
<p>More programming support will be coming soon, according to Microsoft.  The Beta 2 version of Visual Studio LightSwitch also known as ?KittyHawk?  will be made available soon, perhaps by April. Beta 2 will add new capabilities for building business oriented apps that target Windows Azure and SQL Azure.</p>
<p>In face, LightSwitch is a rapid-application-development tool which can be used by new coders with little experience who are interested in designing and building business applications. Microsoft made a public beta of it available in August 2010.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Source: <a href="http://www.microsoft.com/visualstudio/en-us/try?CR_CC=200000862&amp;WT.mc_id=MSCOM_MEDIA&amp;WT.mc_id=MSCOM_DLC_US_PT_113LMUS004262">Microsoft Visual Studio Download</a></p>
