<blockquote><p>Windows 7 might be the most stable and reliable version of Microsoft&#8217;s operating system yet, but things still can and do go wrong.  In this webcast Mike Halsey MVP, the author of Troubleshooting Windows 7 Inside Out, will show you some of the ways you can maximise productivity by using clever troubleshooting techniques.</p></blockquote>
<p>I&#8217;ll be covering everything from the in-built troubleshooting tools in Windows 7 to how you can use these tools to aid in advanced troubleshooting and repair of the operating system.  The webcast will last for one hour and will include a live Q&amp;A session.</p>
<p>You can register for this webcast <a href="http://www.oreillynet.com/pub/e/1835" target="_blank">here</a>, it takes place live at 10am PT, San Francisco, 6pm &#8211; London | 1pm &#8211; New York | Fri, Mar 11th at 5am &#8211; Sydney | Fri, Mar 11th at 3am &#8211; Tokyo | Fri, Mar 11th at 2am &#8211; Beijing | 11:30pm &#8211; Mumbai.</p>
