</div>";s:14:"date_timestamp";i:1299171469;}i:24;a:14:{s:5:"title";s:60:"Internet Explorer 9 Final, Releasing Sooner Than You?d Think";s:4:"link";s:82:"http://www.windows7news.com/2011/03/02/internet-explorer-9-final-releasing-sooner/";s:8:"comments";s:91:"http://www.windows7news.com/2011/03/02/internet-explorer-9-final-releasing-sooner/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Thu, 03 Mar 2011 04:21:35 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:5:"Jason";}s:8:"category";s:73:"Windows 7 NewsbetaBrowserIE9internet explorerInternet Explorer 9Microsoft";s:4:"guid";s:36:"http://www.windows7news.com/?p=10871";s:11:"description";s:124:"MSDNIndia has alerted the world that Internet Explorer 9 will be released in final form on March 24th at Tech.Ed India 2011.";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:4488:"<p>Microsoft often moves at the pace of an old dinosaur, but the Internet Explorer team has really stepped up the pace with Internet Explorer 9. Just a few weeks ago they unveiled the release candidate of the newest version of IE and now MSDNIndia is tweeting that the final is just about ready as well.</p>
<p>Straight from their twitter account, MSDNIndia has alerted the world that Internet Explorer 9 will be released in final form on March 24th at Tech.Ed India 2011.</p>
<p><a rel="attachment wp-att-10872" href="http://www.windows7news.com/2011/03/02/internet-explorer-9-final-releasing-sooner/msdnindia-ie9-400x259/"><img class="size-full wp-image-10872 aligncenter" src="http://wincom.eurekaconsultinglimited.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/msdnindia-ie9-400x259.jpg" alt="msdnindia ie9 400x259 Internet Explorer 9 Final, Releasing Sooner Than Youd Think" width="400" height="259" title="Internet Explorer 9 Final, Releasing Sooner Than Youd Think" /></a></p>
<p>Microsoft notes that the RC of IE9 has been downloaded over 36 million times and this comes on the wave of news that Internet Explorer has gained, ever-so-slightly, in market share overall.</p>
<p>After using the beta of IE9 I was worried that the browser was going to be too buggy and too slow on some loads to make an impact, but after using IE9 RC as my primary browser for the last few weeks, I&#8217;ve come to realize that Microsoft is finally back in the game with the latest version. It&#8217;s fast, compatible and mostly bug-free. And now, it&#8217;s just about finished.</p>
<p>Source: <a href="http://microsoft-news.com/ie9-going-final-being-launched-24th-march-at-tech-ed-india-2011/" target="_blank">Microsoft News</a></p>


