</ol></p><div class="feedflare">
<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/MicrosoftWindows7News?a=88Dp7ERYXg0:DTOCaWCw5eo:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/MicrosoftWindows7News?i=88Dp7ERYXg0:DTOCaWCw5eo:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/MicrosoftWindows7News?a=88Dp7ERYXg0:DTOCaWCw5eo:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/MicrosoftWindows7News?i=88Dp7ERYXg0:DTOCaWCw5eo:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/MicrosoftWindows7News?a=88Dp7ERYXg0:DTOCaWCw5eo:I9og5sOYxJI"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/MicrosoftWindows7News?d=I9og5sOYxJI" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/MicrosoftWindows7News?a=88Dp7ERYXg0:DTOCaWCw5eo:qj6IDK7rITs"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/MicrosoftWindows7News?d=qj6IDK7rITs" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/MicrosoftWindows7News?a=88Dp7ERYXg0:DTOCaWCw5eo:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/MicrosoftWindows7News?i=88Dp7ERYXg0:DTOCaWCw5eo:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/MicrosoftWindows7News?a=88Dp7ERYXg0:DTOCaWCw5eo:F7zBnMyn0Lo"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/MicrosoftWindows7News?i=88Dp7ERYXg0:DTOCaWCw5eo:F7zBnMyn0Lo" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/MicrosoftWindows7News?a=88Dp7ERYXg0:DTOCaWCw5eo:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/MicrosoftWindows7News?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a>
</div>";}s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:78:"http://www.windows7news.com/2011/03/02/global-scale-bing-overtakes-yahoo/feed/";}s:5:"slash";a:1:{s:8:"comments";s:1:"7";}s:7:"summary";s:339:"A report issued today from web analytics company Statcounter, the Bing search engine passed Yahoo! for the first time worldwide in January and increased its lead in February. So here are the numbers. In the global market place, Bing reached 4.37% in February placing it ahead of Yahoo! which came in at 3.93%. It is important to note [...]";s:12:"atom_content";s:7239:"<p>A report issued today from web analytics company <a href="http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20110301006261/en/Bing-Overtakes-Yahoo!-Globally-Time-%E2%80%93-StatCounter">Statcounter</a>, the Bing search engine passed Yahoo! for the first time worldwide in January and increased its lead in February. So here are the numbers. In the global market place, Bing reached 4.37% in February placing it ahead of Yahoo! which came in at 3.93%. It is important to note that both trail far behind Google?s numbers, which are 89.94% of the global search engine market.</p>
<p><a href="http://wincom.eurekaconsultinglimited.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/SearchAllianceBanner.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-10870" src="http://wincom.eurekaconsultinglimited.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/SearchAllianceBanner.jpg" alt="SearchAllianceBanner On a Global Scale Bing Overtakes Yahoo" width="224" height="145" title="On a Global Scale Bing Overtakes Yahoo" /></a></p>
<p>State side in the United States the numbers are different. Yahoo! comes in at 9.74%  which is still over Bing&#8217;s numbers at 9.03%. Meanwhile Google?s share in the US comes in at 79.63%.  If you recall, in July 2009 Microsoft announced an agreement whereby Bing would power the Yahoo! search technology. This agreement has been implemented in the US, Canada, Australia, Brazil and Mexico.</p>
<p><strong>Where the numbers come from</strong></p>
<p>StatCounter,  specializes in website visitor analysis for organisations and bloggers, provides free lifetime stats and free detailed analysis on the latest 500 hits.  The  Global Stats are based on aggregate data collected on a sample of over 15 billion page views per month from across the StatCounter network of more than three million websites.</p>
<p><strong>Yahoo-Bing Search Alliance</strong></p>
<p>One of the upturns from this development is that companies have reason to invest in the search alliance because the system makes web searches more efficient.  The Search Alliance has made it possible to manage two search networks much less time consuming. And from an advertising perspective, Marin Software set out to <a href="http://www.marinsoftware.com/resources/best-practices/the-search-alliance-checklist-whitepaper" target="_blank">study the impact</a> of the transition to help advertisers make informed decisions about investing in the Search Alliance.  Here are three findings from Marin Software&#8217;s research that every search marketer should know about the combined Search Alliance market.</p>
<p><strong>1.  Search Alliance Gains Ground on Google</strong></p>
<p>The Search Alliance gained a small amount of ground on Google in paid search. Specifically, the Search Alliance increased its combined share of paid search clicks by 2 percent, to 21 percent of the total.</p>
<p><strong>2. Improved ROAS</strong></p>
<p>Excluding the impact of seasonality, conversion rates for Search Alliance advertisers increased by 12 percent relative to Google during the study period (August to December 2010). Cost per click, on the other hand, declined by 20 percent relative to Google.</p>
<p><strong>3. There is an advantage by getting in early</strong></p>
<p><strong> </strong>The Search Alliance has upside potential for both Yahoo and Microsoft.  In late 2010, the Search Alliance was delivering 21 percent of paid search clicks, but only capturing 18 percent of the corresponding ad spend in North America. That means the Search Alliance has the potential to capture an additional 3 percent in advertising spend share if CPCs were to rise.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>When advertisers realize the economic potential of the combined platform, they will shift spend to the Search Alliance. When they do, acquisition costs will likely rise. But in the meantime, the Search Alliance is paying healthy dividends for the advertisers who went out to build out and optimize campaigns prior to the transition.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Source: <a href="http://searchenginewatch.com/3641962">SearchEngineWatch</a></strong></p>
<p><strong><a href="http://advertising.microsoft.com/support-center/microsoft-transition-center/yahoo-bing-tips">Microsoft Advertising</a></strong></p>
