</div>";s:14:"date_timestamp";i:1299030349;}i:28;a:14:{s:5:"title";s:43:"Convert Windows 7 ISO Image With Binpatcher";s:4:"link";s:78:"http://www.windows7news.com/2011/03/01/convert-windows-7-iso-image-binpatcher/";s:8:"comments";s:87:"http://www.windows7news.com/2011/03/01/convert-windows-7-iso-image-binpatcher/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Tue, 01 Mar 2011 17:09:50 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:6:"Martin";}s:8:"category";s:79:"Windows 7 SoftwarebinpatcherWindows 7windows 7 dvdwindows 7 isowindows software";s:4:"guid";s:36:"http://www.windows7news.com/?p=10859";s:11:"description";s:319:"Users who download a Windows 7 ISO image from the Internet, for instance from MSDN or Technet, can only use it to install a specific version of the operating system. At least that&#8217;s the default and intended way. It is for instance not possible to install Windows 7 Professional if Windows 7 Home Premium has [...]";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:4892:"<p>Users who download a Windows 7 ISO image from the Internet, for instance from MSDN or Technet, can only use it to install a specific version of the operating system. At least that&#8217;s the default and intended way. It is for instance not possible to install <a href="http://windows7news.com/windows-7-professional/">Windows 7 Professional</a> if <a href="http://windows7news.com/windows-7-home-premium/">Windows 7 Home Premium</a> has been downloaded. Heck, it is not even possible to install the 64-bit edition of <a href="http://windows7news.com/windows-7-ultimate/">Windows 7 Ultimate</a> if only the 32-bit version was downloaded.</p>
<p>Users now have the option to download the additional ISO images that they need, or use a lightweight portable application to create additional editions from existing versions.</p>
<p>Binpatcher is a software program that can can do that. The only restriction is that it can only turn 32-bit editions in other 32-bit editions, and 64-bit editions in other 64-bit editions.</p>
<p>The process is always the same. The user downloads the application <a href="http://forums.mydigitallife.info/threads/8717-Windows-7-ISO-Disc-Image-Utilities">from the</a> official forum thread. The developer adds support for additional language versions whenever possible. </p>
<p>Supported are currently Windows 7 and SP1 editions in English and German, Windows 7 editions in Thai as well as Windows 7 SP1 editions in Dutch, Italian, French, Portuguese, Russian, Spanish and Turkish.</p>
<p>The patch, that is the target edition of Windows 7, needs to be selected from the application directory. Available for selection are 64-bit editions of Home Premium, Professional and Ultimate, and 32-bit editions of Home Basic, Starter, Home Premium, Professional and Ultimate.</p>
<p>Once the target edition has been selected it is time to select the source ISO disc image. The program will do the rest automatically. It patches the source ISO so that it can be used to install the selected edition of Windows 7.</p>
<p>The process helps to save bandwidth as it is now not required to download multiple images from Microsoft or other sources. </p>


